{
  "page": "Lord Baelish (father of Petyr)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Baelish\" title=\"House Baelish\"><img alt=\"House Baelish.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Baelish.svg/50px-House_Baelish.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Baelish.svg/75px-House_Baelish.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9e/House_Baelish.svg/100px-House_Baelish.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Lord Baelish</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Baelish\" title=\"House Baelish\"><img alt=\"House Baelish.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Baelish.svg/50px-House_Baelish.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9e/House_Baelish.svg/75px-House_Baelish.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9e/House_Baelish.svg/100px-House_Baelish.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Lord_Baelish.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Lord Baelish.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d6/Lord_Baelish.png/300px-Lord_Baelish.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"342\" srcset=\"/images/d/d6/Lord_Baelish.png 1.5x\" /></a><div>Lord Baelish as depicted in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i>: <i>Histories &amp; Lore</i>.</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">Lord</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Baelish\" title=\"House Baelish\">House Baelish</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">House Arryn</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Valemen\" title=\"Valemen\">Valemen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nat least several years before <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_256_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">256&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Calculation_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Calculation-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/282_AC\" title=\"282 AC\">282</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_296_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">296&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Calculation_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Calculation-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Baelish_(hedge_knight)\" title=\"Baelish (hedge knight)\">Baelish</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Spouse</th><td>\nLady <a href=\"/index.php/Alayne_Baelish\" title=\"Alayne Baelish\">Alayne</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>father</b> of <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a> was \"the smallest of small lords\" in the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> His first name is unknown.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Baelish_(father_of_Petyr)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>His <a href=\"/index.php/Baelish_(sellsword)\" title=\"Baelish (sellsword)\">grandfather</a> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavosi</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Baelish_(sellsword)\" title=\"Baelish (sellsword)\">sellsword</a> in the service of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Corbray\" title=\"House Corbray\">Corbray</a>, and his <a href=\"/index.php/Baelish_(hedge_knight)\" title=\"Baelish (hedge knight)\">father</a> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Hedge_knight\" title=\"Hedge knight\">hedge knight</a> who took the head of the <a href=\"/index.php/Titan_of_Braavos\" title=\"Titan of Braavos\">Titan of Braavos</a> as his sigil when he was <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knighted</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos68.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_the_Ninepenny_Kings\" title=\"War of the Ninepenny Kings\">War of the Ninepenny Kings</a>, Lord Baelish became friends with Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Hoster_Tully\" title=\"Hoster Tully\">Hoster Tully</a>. He later \"cashed in\" on the friendship to have his son <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Fostered\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fostered\">fostered</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Lord Baelish died several years before the start of the series and was succeeded by his son, Petyr.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lord_Baelish_(father_of_Petyr)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Baelish_(sellsword)\" title=\"Baelish (sellsword)\">Sellsword<br />Baelish</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />wife</td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr><tr align=\"center\"><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</spa